    "These technologies improve prenatal outcomes, particularly in resource-limited settings, where scalable AI-driven diagnostic tools can bridge healthcare gaps (Figure 10) [46,51].AI-driven prenatal diagnostics also present ethical considerations, including algorithmic transparency and the need to validate models across diverse populations [45,52].",
